<paragraph id="8BFD45513601D06956E4FF23FB2C4BBD" blockId="11.[151,1047,220,244]" box="[151,1047,220,244]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="AB52627F3601D06956E4FF23FB2C4BBD" box="[151,1047,220,244]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<treatmentCitation id="0AE363403601D06956E4FF23FD3A4BBD" author="Westwood, J. O." box="[151,513,220,244]" page="444" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" year="1833">
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23601D06956E4FF23FD3A4BBD" authority="Westwood, 1833: 444" authorityName="Westwood" authorityPageNumber="444" authorityYear="1833" box="[151,513,220,244]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Aprostocetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433601D06956E4FF23FE214BBA" box="[151,282,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Aprostocetus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D0695752FF23FD3A4BBD" author="Westwood, J. O." box="[289,513,220,244]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="443 - 445" refId="ref20262" refString="Westwood, J. O. (1833) Descriptions of several new British forms amongst the parasitic hymenopterous insects. Philosophical Magazine Series, 3 (2), 443 - 445. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 14786443308648084" type="journal article" year="1833">Westwood, 1833: 444</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. 
<typeStatus id="54F9FBF33601D0695479FF23FD074BBD" box="[522,572,220,244]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23601D06954EAFF23FC464BBD" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1833" box="[665,893,220,244]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Aprostocetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis id="B93699433601D06954EAFF23FC464BBD" box="[665,893,220,244]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Aprostocetus caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by monotypy.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513601D06956E4FEE6FBCE4A78" blockId="11.[151,1269,281,305]" box="[151,1269,281,305]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
For more complete lists of synonymies see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D069543CFEE6FDD64A78" author="Graham, M. W. R. de V." box="[591,749,281,305]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref18896" refString="Graham, M. W. R. de V. (1987) A reclassification of the European Tetrastichinae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae), with a revision of certain genera. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Entomology Series, 55, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="1987">Graham (1987)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D0695484FEE6FCAA4A78" author="Boucek, Z." box="[759,913,281,305]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref18491" refString="Boucek, Z. (1988) Australasian Chalcidoidea (Hymenoptera): A Biosystematic Revision of Genera of Fourteen Families, with a Reclassification of Species. CAB International, Wallingford, 832 pp." type="book" year="1988">Bouček (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, LaSalle (1994) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D0695217FEE6FBCA4A78" author="Noyes, J. S." box="[1124,1265,281,305]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref20012" refString="Noyes, J. S. (2019) Universal Chalcidoidea Database. World Wide Web electronic publication. Available from: http: // www. nhm. ac. uk / chalcidoids (accessed 9 April 2021)" type="url" year="2019">Noyes (2019)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513601D06956E4FEA0FC43493C" blockId="11.[151,1437,351,738]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23601D06956E4FEA0FE134A30" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1833" box="[151,296,351,377]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Aprostocetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433601D06956E4FEA0FE134A30" box="[151,296,351,377]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Aprostocetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the largest and most diverse genus in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23601D06955FBFEA0FB1E4A30" baseAuthorityName="Narendran" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[904,1061,351,377]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tetrastichinae">Tetrastichinae</taxonomicName>
with about 813 described species worldwide (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D069576CFE7CFE964AD4" author="Noyes, J. S." box="[287,429,387,413]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref20012" refString="Noyes, J. S. (2019) Universal Chalcidoidea Database. World Wide Web electronic publication. Available from: http: // www. nhm. ac. uk / chalcidoids (accessed 9 April 2021)" type="url" year="2019">Noyes 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23601D06957B2FE7CFD694AD4" authority="Westwood" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1833" box="[449,594,387,413]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Aprostocetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433601D06957B2FE7CFD694AD4" box="[449,594,387,413]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Aprostocetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species parasitize a wide variety of hosts, which are often insects inhabiting a variety of plant galls, including 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23601D069544CFE58FDAD4A88" box="[575,662,423,449]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23601D06954D1FE57FC064A8B" box="[674,829,424,450]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23601D069553AFE58FB734A88" authority=", Coccoidea" authorityName="Coccoidea" box="[841,1096,423,449]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera, Coccoidea</taxonomicName>
and even eriophyid mites and nematodes (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D069576DFE34FE874AAC" author="Graham, M. W. R. de V." box="[286,444,459,485]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref18896" refString="Graham, M. W. R. de V. (1987) A reclassification of the European Tetrastichinae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae), with a revision of certain genera. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Entomology Series, 55, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="1987">Graham 1987</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D06957B4FE33FD5C4AAC" author="La Salle, J." box="[455,615,459,486]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="109 - 236" refId="ref19695" refString="La Salle, J. (1994) North American genera of Tetrastichinae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae). Journal of Natural History, 28, 109 - 236. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939400770091" type="journal article" year="1994">La Salle 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Species in the genus exhibit extensive biological and morphological diversity (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D0695682FE10FEF64940" author="La Salle, J. &amp; Arakelian, G. &amp; Garrison, R. W. &amp; Gates, M. W." box="[241,461,495,521]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="35 - 43" refId="ref19819" refString="La Salle, J., Arakelian, G., Garrison, R. W. &amp; Gates, M. W. (2009) A new species of invasive gall wasp (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae: Tetrastichinae) on blue gum (Eucalyptus globulus) in California. Zootaxa, 2121 (4), 35 - 43. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2121.1.4" type="journal article" year="2009">
La Salle 
<emphasis id="B93699433601D0695726FE0FFEB64940" box="[341,397,495,521]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) and it has therefore been subdivided into six subgenera (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D0695239FE10FBDC4940" author="Graham, M. W. R. de V." box="[1098,1255,495,521]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref18896" refString="Graham, M. W. R. de V. (1987) A reclassification of the European Tetrastichinae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae), with a revision of certain genera. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Entomology Series, 55, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="1987">Graham 1987</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D0695281FE0FFAAB4940" author="La Salle, J." box="[1266,1424,495,522]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="109 - 236" refId="ref19695" refString="La Salle, J. (1994) North American genera of Tetrastichinae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae). Journal of Natural History, 28, 109 - 236. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939400770091" type="journal article" year="1994">La Salle 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Generic keys including 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23601D06957DBFDECFD024964" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1833" box="[424,569,531,557]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Aprostocetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433601D06957DBFDECFD024964" box="[424,569,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Aprostocetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are available for Australasia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D06955E1FDECFB164964" author="Boucek, Z." box="[914,1069,531,557]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref18491" refString="Boucek, Z. (1988) Australasian Chalcidoidea (Hymenoptera): A Biosystematic Revision of Genera of Fourteen Families, with a Reclassification of Species. CAB International, Wallingford, 832 pp." type="book" year="1988">Bouček 1988</bibRefCitation>
), North America (LaSalle 1994, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D06956E4FDC8FE4A4918" author="Schauff, M. E. &amp; La Salle, J. &amp; Coote, L. D." box="[151,369,567,593]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="327 - 429" refId="ref20183" refString="Schauff, M. E., La Salle, J. &amp; Coote, L. D. (1997) Eulophidae. In: Gibson, G. A. P., Huber, J. T. &amp; Woolley, J. B. (Eds.), Annotated Keys to the Genera of Nearctic Chalcidoidea (Hymenoptera). National Research Council Research Press, Ottawa, pp. 327 - 429." type="book chapter" year="1997">
Schauff 
<emphasis id="B93699433601D0695686FDC7FE154918" box="[245,302,567,593]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
1997
</bibRefCitation>
), Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D0695797FDC8FDBA4918" author="Graham, M. W. R. de V." box="[484,641,567,593]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref18896" refString="Graham, M. W. R. de V. (1987) A reclassification of the European Tetrastichinae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae), with a revision of certain genera. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Entomology Series, 55, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="1987">Graham 1987</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F35505C13601D06954B3FDC8FDC14918" box="[704,762,567,593]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D069557AFDC8FCF94918" author="Narendran, T. C." box="[777,962,567,593]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref19965" refString="Narendran, T. C. (2007) Indian chalcidoid parasitoids of the Tetrastichinae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae). Records Zoological Survey of India, Occasional Paper No. 272. Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata, 386 pp., 4 pls." type="book" year="2007">Narendran 2007</bibRefCitation>
) but keys to species are available only for the European (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D0695749FDA4FEED493C" author="Graham, M. W. R. de V." box="[314,470,603,629]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref18896" refString="Graham, M. W. R. de V. (1987) A reclassification of the European Tetrastichinae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae), with a revision of certain genera. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Entomology Series, 55, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="1987">Graham 1987</bibRefCitation>
) and Indian (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03601D0695418FDA4FC1F493C" author="Narendran, T. C." box="[619,804,603,629]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref19965" refString="Narendran, T. C. (2007) Indian chalcidoid parasitoids of the Tetrastichinae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae). Records Zoological Survey of India, Occasional Paper No. 272. Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata, 386 pp., 4 pls." type="book" year="2007">Narendran 2007</bibRefCitation>
) fauna.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513601D06956B4FD80FB6849A8" blockId="11.[151,1437,351,738]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Both species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23601D06957F2FD80FD2949D0" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1833" box="[385,530,639,665]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Aprostocetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433601D06957F2FD80FD2949D0" box="[385,530,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Aprostocetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reared from leaf vein galls of 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23601D0695500FD7FFB3349D0" box="[883,1032,639,665]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapotaceae" genus="Madhuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longifolia">
